# Stripe — CCNA Timed Test Simulation (Checkout + webhook)
# Copy to .env.local for local CLI testing; set the same keys in Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables.
#
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY must be the Secret key (sk_test_… / sk_live_…) from Developers → API keys,
# or a Restricted key (rk_test_… / rk_live_…) with permission for Checkout. Not mk_, pk_, or whsec_.
# Webhook signing secret (whsec_…) goes in STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET only.
# Use the secret from the webhook whose URL is THIS site (e.g. https://becertifiedtoday.com/api/stripe-webhook).
# If your Stripe webhook points at another Vercel app (e.g. becertifiedtoday-encor.vercel.app), add a second
# endpoint in Stripe for this domain and put that endpoint’s whsec_ here.

STRIPE_SECRET_KEY=sk_test_xxxxxxxx
STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET=whsec_xxxxxxxx

# One-time Price for the simulated test (Stripe Dashboard → Products → Price ID)
STRIPE_PRICE_CCNA_TEST_SIM=price_xxxxxxxx

# Site origin for Checkout success/cancel redirects. Must match how users open the site (www vs apex).
# Code adds https:// if missing and strips paths/trailing slashes/stray quotes.
PUBLIC_SITE_URL=https://becertifiedtoday.com

# --- After payment ---
# • If payment succeeds but the browser never lands on the timed test, set PUBLIC_SITE_URL to the exact
#   origin you use (e.g. https://www.becertifiedtoday.com vs https://becertifiedtoday.com).
# • Stripe receipt emails: Dashboard → Settings → Emails → enable receipts for successful payments.
#   This repo does not send custom receipt email yet; /api/stripe-webhook only verifies events when
#   STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET is set (optional for redirect; required for webhook delivery).
